A set of rare 'mono mono' twins born holding hands in Ohio are going to be home in time for Father's Day.

Jenna and Jillian Thistlethwaite were born May 9 sharing an amniotic sac and placenta at Akron General Medical Center, in the state's northwest.

After spending nearly a month in the hospital's neonatal intensive care unit, the Akron Beacon Journal reports that the identical twins went home in Orrville in northeast Ohio on Saturday.

