Their father, Bill Thistlethwaite, says he's excited to have the girls at home with him, his wife and their 15-month-old son, Jaxon.

He said he
 and his wife, Sarah, were approached by people Saturday while having 
breakfast at a diner in their hometown of Orrville before going to visit
 the girls.

They want to know how the twins are doing and express their 
good wishes, he said.

Both girls are taking full bottles and have gained weight, each now at five pounds or more.

The twins' rare birth condition is called monoamnioitic, or 'mono mono'.

Doctors say they occur in about one of every 10,000 pregnancies.

